simlockd (0.3.0) stable; urgency=low

  * If no SIM card is present the phone will now always be locked
  * Added console commands including "clear" and "show" to allow basic management
  * Notifications are now shown to indicate activity by the daemon
  * Made sure that IMSI numbers do not contain non-printable characters or whitespace
  * Installation generates required symlinks automatically now and sets executable permissions

 -- Benjamin Pannell <contact@sierrasoftworks.com> Sun, 19 Jun 2011 10:20:15 +0200

simlockd (0.2.0) stable; urgency=low

  * Fixed a bug that caused SIMLockD to never exit if the IMEI was valid
  * Made the Allowed IMSI database's location static
  * Made the daemon start on bootup
  * Daemon will not be launched until /opt is mounted
  * Added an icon to the deb package
  * Made simlockd wait for 10 seconds before locking the device on startup
  * Made simlockd only run once, on startup

 -- Benjamin Pannell <contact@sierrasoftworks.com> Sun, 05 Jun 2011 19:28:00 +0200

simlockd (0.1.0) stable; urgency=low

  * Fixed problems with locking of the phone
  * Phone will now enter offline mode when locked to prevent SSH attacks
  * When the phone is unlocked after an automatic lock it will now add the IMSI to the list of allowed ones

 -- Benjamin Pannell <contact@sierrasoftworks.com> Sun, 05 Jun 2011 15:47:00 +0200

simlockd (0.0.1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Initial Release.

 -- Benjamin Pannell <contact@sierrasoftworks.com>  Sun, 05 Jun 2011 13:02:33 +0200
